# Data Description   ----
#----------------------------------------#

#### // The dataset consists of 7,037 point observations representing 311 service requests related to unsanitary pigeon conditions in New York City from 2020 to the present. Each record contains spatial coordinates (latitude/longitude), complaint descriptors, addresses, and timestamps. The data are stored as a vector point layer in a GeoPackage format using the WGS 84 geographic coordinate system. Spatial extent covers all five NYC boroughs. Initial exploration identified a small number of empty geometries and non-numeric coordinate fields, which were removed or corrected. The cleaned dataset provides a geocoded representation of reported human–pigeon conflict locations suitable for spatial hotspot and proximity analysis.//


